MAINTOWN

This program (actually a SHELL built-in) is a maintenance utility that
ensures that specified directory trees (or files) are owned by the
specified user.

Synopsis:

$ maintown [-r] [-n] <username> [<file(s) ...>] [-af <argfile>] [-f] [-V]

where:

-r		recurse into subdirectories
-c		no stopping on stupid errors!
<username>	username to own directories
<file(s)>	the files or directories
-af <argfile>	more file (or directory) arguments in this file
-f		follow symbolic links
-V		print version to STDERR and exit

